;; task: valid-parens
;; goal: Write (valid-parens? s) that checks if parentheses [] {} () are balanced, test with "({[]})"
;; expect: #t
;; hint: Convert string to char codes: (string->list s) -> list of integers
;; hint: Use a stack: (let loop ((cs chars) (stack ())) ...)
;; hint: Char codes: 40=( 41=)  91=[ 93=]  123={ 125=}
;; hint: Opening bracket -> push its CODE onto stack for matching later
;; hint: Closing bracket -> check if (car stack) matches the corresponding opening code
;; hint:   e.g., for ) (41): (and (pair? stack) (= (car stack) 40)) means match
;; hint: At end, must return (null? stack) — empty stack means balanced
;; hint: (display (valid-parens? "({[]})"))
